        <p>
		<b>JRuby</b> is a pure Java implementation of the <a href="http://www.ruby-lang.org">Ruby</a> interpreter, being developed by <a href="mailto:jpetersen@uni-bonn.de">Jan Arne Petersen</a> and <a href="team.html">others</a>.
	</p><p>
	<b>JRuby</b> is free software released under the GNU General Public License.
        </p><p>
	  <b>JRuby</b> is tightly integrated with Java to allow both to script any Java class and to embed the interpreter into any Java application.
        </p><p><h3>Features</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ruby 1.6.7 compatible interpreter. (Not all builtin classes are supported yet!)</li>
            <li>Support for scripting Java classes and interfaces in JRuby.</li>
            <li>Bean Scripting Framework (BSF) support.</li>
	  </ul>
	</p>
